@file\n * Handles AJAX fetching of views, including filter submission and response.\n */\n(function ($) {\n\n  /**\n   * Attaches the AJAX behavior to exposed filter forms and key views links.\n   */\n  Drupal.behaviors.ViewsAjaxView = {};\n  Drupal.behaviors.ViewsAjaxView.attach = function() {\n    if (Drupal.settings && Drupal.settings.views && Drupal.settings.views.ajaxViews) {\n      $.each(Drupal.settings.views.ajaxViews, function(i, settings) {\n        Drupal.views.instances[i] = new Drupal.views.ajaxView(settings);\n      });\n    }\n  };\n\n  Drupal.views = {};\n  Drupal.views.instances = {};\n\n  /**\n   * JavaScript object for a certain view.\n   */\n  Drupal.views.ajaxView = function(settings) {\n    var selector = '.view-dom-id-' + settings.view_dom_id;\n    this.$view = $(selector);\n\n    // Retrieve the path to use for views' ajax.\n    var ajax_path = Drupal.settings.views.ajax_path;\n\n    // If there are multiple views this might've ended up showing up multiple\n    // times.\n    if (ajax_path.constructor.toString().indexOf(\"Array\") != -1) {\n      ajax_path = ajax_path[0];\n    }\n\n    // Check if there are any GET parameters to send to views.\n    var queryString = window.location.search || '';\n    if (queryString !== '') {\n      // Remove the question mark and Drupal path component if any.\n      var queryString = queryString.slice(1).replace(/q=[^&]+&?|&?render=[^&]+/, '');\n      if (queryString !== '') {\n        // If there is a '?' in ajax_path, clean url are on and & should be\n        // used to add parameters.\n        queryString = ((/\\?/.test(ajax_path)) ? '&' : '?') + queryString;\n      }\n    }\n\n    this.element_settings = {\n      url: ajax_path + queryString,\n      submit: settings,\n      setClick: true,\n      event: 'click',\n      selector: selector,\n      progress: {\n        type: 'throbber'\n      }\n    };\n\n    this.settings = settings;\n\n    // Add the ajax to exposed forms.\n    this.$exposed_form = $('#views-exposed-form-' + settings.view_name.replace(/_/g, '-') + '-' + settings.view_display_id.replace(/_/g, '-'));\n    this.$exposed_form.once(jQuery.proxy(this.attachExposedFormAjax, this));\n\n    // Store Drupal.ajax objects here for all pager links.\n    this.links = [];\n\n    // Add the ajax to pagers.\n    this.$view\n      .once(jQuery.proxy(this.attachPagerAjax, this));\n\n    // Add a trigger to update this view specifically. In order to trigger a\n    // refresh use the following code.\n    //\n    // @code\n    // jQuery('.view-name').trigger('RefreshView');\n    // @endcode\n    // Add a trigger to update this view specifically.\n    var self_settings = this.element_settings;\n    self_settings.event = 'RefreshView';\n    var self = this;\n    this.$view.once('refresh', function () {\n      self.refreshViewAjax = new Drupal.ajax(self.selector, self.$view, self_settings);\n    });\n  };\n\n  Drupal.views.ajaxView.prototype.attachExposedFormAjax = function() {\n    var button = $('input[type=submit], button[type=submit], input[type=image]', this.$exposed_form);\n    button = button[0];\n\n    // Call the autocomplete submit before doing AJAX.\n    $(button).click(function () {\n      if (Drupal.autocompleteSubmit) {\n        Drupal.autocompleteSubmit();\n      }\n    });\n\n    this.exposedFormAjax = new Drupal.ajax($(button).attr('id'), button, this.element_settings);\n  };\n\n  /**\n   * Attach the ajax behavior to each link.\n   */\n  Drupal.views.ajaxView.prototype.attachPagerAjax = function() {\n    this.$view.find('ul.pager > li > a, ol.pager > li > a, th.views-field a, .attachment .views-summary a')\n      .each(jQuery.proxy(this.attachPagerLinkAjax, this));\n  };\n\n  /**\n   * Attach the ajax behavior to a single link.\n   */\n  Drupal.views.ajaxView.prototype.attachPagerLinkAjax = function(id, link) {\n    var $link = $(link);\n    var viewData = {};\n    var href = $link.attr('href');\n    // Don't attach to pagers inside nested views.\n    if ($link.closest('.view')[0] !== this.$view[0] &&\n      $link.closest('.view').parent().hasClass('attachment') === false) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Provide a default page if none has been set. This must be done\n    // prior to merging with settings to avoid accidentally using the\n    // page landed on instead of page 1.\n    if (typeof(viewData.page) === 'undefined') {\n      viewData.page = 0;\n    }\n\n    // Construct an object using the settings defaults and then overriding\n    // with data specific to the link.\n    $.extend(\n      viewData,\n      this.settings,\n      Drupal.Views.parseQueryString(href),\n      // Extract argument data from the URL.\n      Drupal.Views.parseViewArgs(href, this.settings.view_base_path)\n    );\n\n    // For anchor tags, these will go to the target of the anchor rather\n    // than the usual location.\n    $.extend(viewData, Drupal.Views.parseViewArgs(href, this.settings.view_base_path));\n\n    this.element_settings.submit = viewData;\n    this.pagerAjax = new Drupal.ajax(false, $link, this.element_settings);\n    this.links.push(this.pagerAjax);\n  };\n\n  Drupal.ajax.prototype.commands.viewsScrollTop = function (ajax, response, status) {\n    // Scroll to the top of the view. This will allow users\n    // to browse newly loaded content after e.g. clicking a pager\n    // link.\n    var offset = $(response.selector).offset();\n    // We can't guarantee that the scrollable object should be\n    // the body, as the view could be embedded in something\n    // more complex such as a modal popup. Recurse up the DOM\n    // and scroll the first element that has a non-zero top.\n    var scrollTarget = response.selector;\n    while ($(scrollTarget).scrollTop() == 0 && $(scrollTarget).parent()) {\n      scrollTarget = $(scrollTarget).parent();\n    }\n    // Only scroll upward.\n    if (offset.top - 10 < $(scrollTarget).scrollTop()) {\n      $(scrollTarget).animate({scrollTop: (offset.top - 10)}, 500);\n    }\n  };\n\n})(jQuery);\n;\n/*!\n * jQuery Remove Uppercase Accents for Drupal 7\n * https://www.drupal.org/project/rua\n *\n * Automatically removes accented characters (currently Greek) from elements\n * having their text content uppercase transformed through CSS.\n *\n * It WILL NOT target fieldset and elements capitalized inside fieldsets!\n */\n\n(function($) {\n\n  $.extend($.expr[\":\"], {\n    uppercase: function(elem) {\n      var attr = $(elem).css(\"text-transform\");\n      return typeof attr !== \"undefined\" && attr === \"uppercase\";\n    },\n    smallcaps: function(elem) {\n      var attr = $(elem).css(\"font-variant\");\n      return typeof attr !== \"undefined\" && attr === \"small-caps\";\n    }\n  });\n\n  $.extend({\n    removeAcc: function(elem) {\n      if (elem.tagName.toLowerCase() === \"input\") {\n        var text = elem.value;\n        text = removeAcc(text);\n        elem.value = text;\n      }\n      else {\n        var childNodes = elem.childNodes;\n        for (var child in childNodes){\n          var nodeType = childNodes[child].nodeType;\n          // Only replace text nodes\n          // @see http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html\n  */\n\n(function($){\n  $.fn.sfsmallscreen = function(options){\n    options = $.extend({\n      mode: 'inactive',\n      type: 'accordion',\n      breakpoint: 768,\n      breakpointUnit: 'px',\n      useragent: '',\n      title: '',\n      addSelected: false,\n      menuClasses: false,\n      hyperlinkClasses: false,\n      excludeClass_menu: '',\n      excludeClass_hyperlink: '',\n      includeClass_menu: '',\n      includeClass_hyperlink: '',\n      accordionButton: 1,\n      expandText: 'Expand',\n      collapseText: 'Collapse'\n    }, options);\n\n    // We need to clean up the menu from anything unnecessary.\n    function refine(menu){\n      var\n      refined = menu.clone(),\n      // Things that should not be in the small-screen menus.\n      rm = refined.find('span.sf-sub-indicator, span.sf-description'),\n      // This is a helper class for those who need to add extra markup that shouldn't exist\n      // in the small-screen versions.\n      rh = refined.find('.sf-smallscreen-remove'),\n      // Mega-menus has to be removed too.\n      mm = refined.find('ul.sf-megamenu');\n      for (var a = 0; a < rh.length; a++){\n        rh.eq(a).replaceWith(rh.eq(a).html());\n      }\n      for (var b = 0; b < rm.length; b++){\n        rm.eq(b).remove();\n      }\n      if (mm.length > 0){\n        mm.removeClass('sf-megamenu');\n        var ol = refined.find('div.sf-megamenu-column > ol');\n        for (var o = 0; o < ol.length; o++){\n          ol.eq(o).replaceWith('<ul>' + ol.eq(o).html() + '</ul>');\n        }\n        var elements = ['div.sf-megamenu-column','.sf-megamenu-wrapper > ol','li.sf-megamenu-wrapper'];\n        for (var i = 0; i < elements.length; i++){\n          obj = refined.find(elements[i]);\n          for (var t = 0; t < obj.length; t++){\n            obj.eq(t).replaceWith(obj.eq(t).html());\n          }\n        }\n        refined.find('.sf-megamenu-column').removeClass('sf-megamenu-column');\n      }\n      refined.add(refined.find('*')).css({width:''});\n      return refined;\n    }\n\n    // Creating <option> elements out of the menu.\n    function toSelect(menu, level){\n      var\n      items = '',\n      childLI = $(menu).children('li');\n      for (var a = 0; a < childLI.length; a++){\n        var list = childLI.eq(a), parent = list.children('a, span');\n        for (var b = 0; b < parent.length; b++){\n          var\n          item = parent.eq(b),\n          path = item.is('a') ? item.attr('href') : '',\n          // Class names modification.\n          itemClone = item.clone(),\n          classes = (options.hyperlinkClasses) ? ((options.excludeClass_hyperlink && itemClone.hasClass(options.excludeClass_hyperlink)) ? itemClone.removeClass(options.excludeClass_hyperlink).attr('class') : itemClone.attr('class')) : '',\n          classes = (options.includeClass_hyperlink && !itemClone.hasClass(options.includeClass_hyperlink)) ? ((options.hyperlinkClasses) ? itemClone.addClass(options.includeClass_hyperlink).attr('class') : options.includeClass_hyperlink) : classes;\n          // Retaining the active class if requested.\n          if (options.addSelected && item.hasClass('active')){\n            classes += ' active';\n          }\n          // <option> has to be disabled if the item is not a link.\n          disable = item.is('span') || item.attr('href')=='#' ? ' disabled=\"disabled\"' : '',\n          // Crystal clear.\n          subIndicator = 1 < level ? Array(level).join('-') + ' ' : '';\n          // Preparing the <option> element.\n          items += '<option value=\"' + path + '\" class=\"' + classes + '\"' + disable + '>' + subIndicator + $.trim(item.text()) +'</option>',\n          childUL = list.find('> ul');\n          // Using the function for the sub-menu of this item.\n          for (var u = 0; u < childUL.length; u++){\n            items += toSelect(childUL.eq(u), level + 1);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      return items;\n    }\n\n    // Create the new version, hide the original.\n    function convert(menu){\n      var menuID = menu.attr('id'),\n      // Creating a refined version of the menu.\n      refinedMenu = refine(menu);\n      // Currently the plugin provides two reactions to small screens.\n      // Converting the menu to a <select> element, and converting to an accordion version of the menu.\n      if (options.type == 'accordion'){\n        var\n        toggleID = menuID + '-toggle',\n        accordionID = menuID + '-accordion';\n        // Making sure the accordion does not exist.\n        if ($('#' + accordionID).length == 0){\n          var\n          // Getting the style class.\n          styleClass = menu.attr('class').split(' ').filter(function(item){\n            return item.indexOf('sf-style-') > -1 ? item : '';\n          }),\n          // Creating the accordion.\n          accordion = $(refinedMenu).attr('id', accordionID);\n          // Removing unnecessary classes.\n          accordion.removeClass('sf-horizontal sf-vertical sf-navbar sf-shadow sf-js-enabled');\n          // Adding necessary classes.\n          accordion.addClass('sf-accordion sf-hidden');\n          // Removing style attributes and any unnecessary class.\n          accordion.children('li').removeAttr('style').removeClass('sfHover');\n          // Doing the same and making sure all the sub-menus are off-screen (hidden).\n          accordion.find('ul').removeAttr('style').not('.sf-hidden').addClass('sf-hidden');\n          // Creating the accordion toggle switch.\n          var toggle = '<div class=\"sf-accordion-toggle ' + styleClass + '\"><a href=\"#\" id=\"' + toggleID + '\"><span>' + options.title + '</span></a></div>';\n\n          // Adding Expand\\Collapse buttons if requested.\n          if (options.accordionButton == 2){\n            var parent = accordion.find('li.menuparent');\n            for (var i = 0; i < parent.length; i++){\n              parent.eq(i).prepend('<a href=\"#\" class=\"sf-accordion-button\">' + options.expandText + '</a>');\n            }\n          }\n          // Inserting the according and hiding the original menu.\n          menu.before(toggle).before(accordion).hide();\n\n          var\n          accordionElement = $('#' + accordionID),\n          // Deciding what should be used as accordion buttons.\n          buttonElement = (options.accordionButton < 2) ? 'a.menuparent,span.nolink.menuparent' : 'a.sf-accordion-button',\n          button = accordionElement.find(buttonElement);\n\n          // Attaching a click event to the toggle switch.\n          $('#' + toggleID).bind('click', function(e){\n            // Preventing the click.\n            e.preventDefault();\n            // Adding the sf-expanded class.\n            $(this).toggleClass('sf-expanded');\n\n            if (accordionElement.hasClass('sf-expanded')){\n              // If the accordion is already expanded:\n              // Hiding its expanded sub-menus and then the accordion itself as well.\n              accordionElement.add(accordionElement.find('li.sf-expanded')).removeClass('sf-expanded')\n              .end().find('ul').hide()\n              // This is a bit tricky, it's the same trick that has been in use in the main plugin for sometime.\n              // Basically we'll add a class that keeps the sub-menu off-screen and still visible,\n              // and make it invisible and removing the class one moment before showing or hiding it.\n              // This helps screen reader software access all the menu items.\n              .end().hide().addClass('sf-hidden').show();\n              // Changing the caption of any existing accordion buttons to 'Expand'.\n              if (options.accordionButton == 2){\n                accordionElement.find('a.sf-accordion-button').text(options.expandText);\n              }\n            }\n            else {\n              // But if it's collapsed,\n              accordionElement.addClass('sf-expanded').hide().removeClass('sf-hidden').show();\n            }\n          });\n\n          // Attaching a click event to the buttons.\n          button.bind('click', function(e){\n            // Making sure the buttons does not exist already.\n            if ($(this).closest('li').children('ul').length > 0){\n              e.preventDefault();\n              // Selecting the parent menu items.\n              var parent = $(this).closest('li');\n              // Creating and inserting Expand\\Collapse buttons to the parent menu items,\n              // of course only if not already happened.\n              if (options.accordionButton == 1 && parent.children('a.menuparent,span.nolink.menuparent').length > 0 && parent.children('ul').children('li.sf-clone-parent').length == 0){\n                var\n                // Cloning the hyperlink of the parent menu item.\n                cloneLink = parent.children('a.menuparent,span.nolink.menuparent').clone(),\n                // Wrapping the hyerplinks in <li>.\n                cloneLink = $('<li class=\"sf-clone-parent\" />').html(cloneLink);\n                // Adding a helper class and attaching them to the sub-menus.\n                parent.children('ul').addClass('sf-has-clone-parent').prepend(cloneLink);\n              }\n              // Once the button is clicked, collapse the sub-menu if it's expanded.\n              if (parent.hasClass('sf-expanded')){\n                parent.children('ul').slideUp('fast', function(){\n                  // Doing the accessibility trick after hiding the sub-menu.\n                  $(this).closest('li').removeClass('sf-expanded').end().addClass('sf-hidden').show();\n                });\n                // Changing the caption of the inserted Collapse link to 'Expand', if any is inserted.\n                if (options.accordionButton == 2 && parent.children('.sf-accordion-button').length > 0){\n                  parent.children('.sf-accordion-button').text(options.expandText);\n                }\n              }\n              // Otherwise, expand the sub-menu.\n              else {\n                // Doing the accessibility trick and then showing the sub-menu.\n                parent.children('ul').hide().removeClass('sf-hidden').slideDown('fast')\n                // Changing the caption of the inserted Expand link to 'Collape', if any is inserted.\n                .end().addClass('sf-expanded').children('a.sf-accordion-button').text(options.collapseText)\n                // Hiding any expanded sub-menu of the same level.\n                .end().siblings('li.sf-expanded').children('ul')\n                .slideUp('fast', function(){\n                  // Doing the accessibility trick after hiding it.\n                  $(this).closest('li').removeClass('sf-expanded').end().addClass('sf-hidden').show();\n                })\n                // Assuming Expand\\Collapse buttons do exist, resetting captions, in those hidden sub-menus.\n                .parent().children('a.sf-accordion-button').text(options.expandText);\n              }\n            }\n          });\n        }\n      }\n      else {\n        var\n        // Class names modification.\n        menuClone = menu.clone(), classes = (options.menuClasses) ? ((options.excludeClass_menu && menuClone.hasClass(options.excludeClass_menu)) ? menuClone.removeClass(options.excludeClass_menu).attr('class') : menuClone.attr('class')) : '',\n        classes = (options.includeClass_menu && !menuClone.hasClass(options.includeClass_menu)) ? ((options.menuClasses) ? menuClone.addClass(options.includeClass_menu).attr('class') : options.includeClass_menu) : classes,\n        classes = (classes) ? ' class=\"' + classes + '\"' : '';\n\n        // Making sure the <select> element does not exist already.\n        if ($('#' + menuID + '-select').length == 0){\n          // Creating the <option> elements.\n          var newMenu = toSelect(refinedMenu, 1),\n          // Creating the <select> element and assigning an ID and class name.\n          selectList = $('<select' + classes + ' id=\"' + menuID + '-select\"/>')\n          // Attaching the title and the items to the <select> element.\n          .html('<option>' + options.title + '</option>' + newMenu)\n          // Attaching an event then.\n          .change(function(){\n            // Except for the first option that is the menu title and not a real menu item.\n            if ($('option:selected', this).index()){\n              window.location = selectList.val();\n            }\n          });\n          // Applying the addSelected option to it.\n          if (options.addSelected){\n            selectList.find('.active').attr('selected', !0);\n          }\n          // Finally inserting the <select> element into the document then hiding the original menu.\n          menu.before(selectList).hide();\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Turn everything back to normal.\n    function turnBack(menu){\n      var\n      id = '#' + menu.attr('id');\n      // Removing the small screen version.\n      $(id + '-' + options.type).remove();\n      // Removing the accordion toggle switch as well.\n      if (options.type == 'accordion'){\n        $(id + '-toggle').parent('div').remove();\n      }\n      // Crystal clear!\n      $(id).show();\n    }\n\n    // Return original object to support chaining.\n    // Although this is unnecessary because of the way the module uses these plugins.\n    for (var s = 0; s < this.length; s++){\n      var\n      menu = $(this).eq(s),\n      mode = options.mode;\n      // The rest is crystal clear, isn't it? :)\n      if (mode == 'always_active'){\n        convert(menu);\n      }\n      else if (mode == 'window_width'){\n        var breakpoint = (options.breakpointUnit == 'em') ? (options.breakpoint * parseFloat($('body').css('font-size'))) : options.breakpoint,\n        windowWidth = window.innerWidth || document.documentElement.clientWidth || document.body.clientWidth,\n        timer;\n        if ((typeof Modernizr === 'undefined' || typeof Modernizr.mq !== 'function') && windowWidth < breakpoint){\n          convert(menu);\n        }\n        else if (typeof Modernizr !== 'undefined' && typeof Modernizr.mq === 'function' && Modernizr.mq('(max-width:' + (breakpoint - 1) + 'px)')) {\n          convert(menu);\n        }\n        $(window).resize(function(){\n          clearTimeout(timer);\n          timer = setTimeout(function(){\n            var windowWidth = window.innerWidth || document.documentElement.clientWidth || document.body.clientWidth;\n            if ((typeof Modernizr === 'undefined' || typeof Modernizr.mq !== 'function') && windowWidth < breakpoint){\n              convert(menu);\n            }\n            else if (typeof Modernizr !== 'undefined' && typeof Modernizr.mq === 'function' && Modernizr.mq('(max-width:' + (breakpoint - 1) + 'px)')) {\n              convert(menu);\n            }\n            else {\n              turnBack(menu);\n            }\n          }, 50);\n        });\n      }\n      else if (mode == 'useragent_custom'){\n        if (options.useragent != ''){\n          var ua = RegExp(options.useragent, 'i');\n          if (navigator.userAgent.match(ua)){\n            convert(menu);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      else if (mode == 'useragent_predefined' && navigator.userAgent.match(/(android|bb\\d+|meego).+mobile|avantgo|bada\\/|blackberry|blazer|compal|elaine|fennec|hiptop|iemobile|ip(hone|od|ad)|iris|kindle|lge |maemo|midp|mmp|netfront|opera m(ob|in)i|palm( os)?|phone|p(ixi|re)\\/|plucker|pocket|psp|series(4|6)0|symbian|treo|up\\.(browser|link)|vodafone|wap|windows (ce|phone)|xda|xiino/i)){\n        convert(menu);\n      }\n    }\n    return this;\n  }\n})(jQuery);\n;\n/*\n * Supposition v0.2 - an optional enhancer for Superfish jQuery menu widget.\n *\n * Copyright (c) 2008 Joel Birch - based mostly on work by Jesse Klaasse and credit goes largely to him.\n * Special thanks to Karl Swedberg for valuable input.\n *\n * Dual licensed under the MIT and GPL licenses:\n *  http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php\n *  http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html\n */\n/*\n * This is not the original jQuery Supposition plugin.\n * Please refer to the README for more information.\n */\n\n(function($){\n  $.fn.supposition = function(){\n    var $w = $(window), /*do this once instead of every onBeforeShow call*/\n    _offset = function(dir) {\n      return window[dir == 'y' ? 'pageYOffset' : 'pageXOffset']\n      || document.documentElement && document.documentElement[dir=='y' ? 'scrollTop' : 'scrollLeft']\n      || document.body[dir=='y' ? 'scrollTop' : 'scrollLeft'];\n    },\n    onHide = function(){\n      this.css({bottom:''});\n    },\n    onBeforeShow = function(){\n      this.each(function(){\n        var $u = $(this);\n        $u.css('display','block');\n        var $mul = $u.closest('.sf-menu'),\n        level = $u.parents('ul').length,\n        menuWidth = $u.width(),\n        menuParentWidth = $u.closest('li').outerWidth(true),\n        menuParentLeft = $u.closest('li').offset().left,\n        totalRight = $w.width() + _offset('x'),\n        menuRight = $u.offset().left + menuWidth,\n        exactMenuWidth = (menuRight > (menuParentWidth + menuParentLeft)) ? menuWidth - (menuRight - (menuParentWidth + menuParentLeft)) : menuWidth;\n        if ($u.parents('.sf-js-enabled').hasClass('rtl')) {\n          if (menuParentLeft < exactMenuWidth) {\n            if (($mul.hasClass('sf-horizontal') && level == 1) || ($mul.hasClass('sf-navbar') && level == 2)){\n              $u.css({left:0,right:'auto'});\n            }\n            else {\n              $u.css({left:menuParentWidth + 'px',right:'auto'});\n            }\n          }\n        }\n        else {\n          if (menuRight > totalRight && menuParentLeft > menuWidth) {\n            if (($mul.hasClass('sf-horizontal') && level == 1) || ($mul.hasClass('sf-navbar') && level == 2)){\n              $u.css({right:0,left:'auto'});\n            }\n            else {\n              $u.css({right:menuParentWidth + 'px',left:'auto'});\n            }\n          }\n        }\n        var windowHeight = $w.height(),\n        offsetTop = $u.offset().top,\n        menuParentShadow = ($mul.hasClass('sf-shadow') && $u.css('padding-bottom').length > 0) ? parseInt($u.css('padding-bottom').slice(0,-2)) : 0,\n        menuParentHeight = ($mul.hasClass('sf-vertical')) ? '-' + menuParentShadow : $u.parent().outerHeight(true) - menuParentShadow,\n        menuHeight = $u.height(),\n        baseline = windowHeight + _offset('y');\n        var expandUp = ((offsetTop + menuHeight > baseline) && (offsetTop > menuHeight));\n        if (expandUp) {\n          $u.css({bottom:menuParentHeight + 'px',top:'auto'});\n        }\n        $u.css('display','none');\n      });\n    };\n\n    return this.each(function() {\n      var o = $.fn.superfish.o[this.serial]; /* get this menu's options */\n\n      /* if callbacks already set, store them */\n      var _onBeforeShow = o.onBeforeShow,\n      _onHide = o.onHide;\n\n      $.extend($.fn.superfish.o[this.serial],{\n        onBeforeShow: function() {\n          onBeforeShow.call(this); /* fire our Supposition callback */\n          _onBeforeShow.call(this); /* fire stored callbacks */\n        },\n        onHide: function() {\n          onHide.call(this); /* fire our Supposition callback */\n          _onHide.call(this); /* fire stored callbacks */\n        }\n      });\n    });\n  };\n})(jQuery);;\n/*\n * Superfish v1.4.8 - jQuery menu widget\n * Copyright (c) 2008 Joel Birch\n *\n * Dual licensed under the MIT and GPL licenses:\n *  http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php\n *  http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html\n *\n * CHANGELOG: http://users.tpg.com.au/j_birch/plugins/superfish/changelog.txt\n */\n/*\n * This is not the original jQuery Superfish plugin.\n * Please refer to the README for more information.\n */\n\n(function($){\n  $.fn.superfish = function(op){\n    var sf = $.fn.superfish,\n      c = sf.c,\n      $arrow = $(['<span class=\"',c.arrowClass,'\"> &#187;</span>'].join('')),\n      over = function(){\n        var $$ = $(this), menu = getMenu($$);\n        clearTimeout(menu.sfTimer);\n        $$.showSuperfishUl().siblings().hideSuperfishUl();\n      },\n      out = function(){\n        var $$ = $(this), menu = getMenu($$), o = sf.op;\n        clearTimeout(menu.sfTimer);\n        menu.sfTimer=setTimeout(function(){\n          if ($$.children('.sf-clicked').length == 0){\n            o.retainPath=($.inArray($$[0],o.$path)>-1);\n            $$.hideSuperfishUl();\n            if (o.$path.length && $$.parents(['li.',o.hoverClass].join('')).length<1){over.call(o.$path);}\n          }\n        },o.delay);\n      },\n      getMenu = function($menu){\n        var menu = $menu.parents(['ul.',c.menuClass,':first'].join(''))[0];\n        sf.op = sf.o[menu.serial];\n        return menu;\n      },\n      addArrow = function($a){ $a.addClass(c.anchorClass).append($arrow.clone()); };\n\n    return this.each(function() {\n      var s = this.serial = sf.o.length;\n      var o = $.extend({},sf.defaults,op);\n      o.$path = $('li.'+o.pathClass,this).slice(0,o.pathLevels),\n      p = o.$path;\n      for (var l = 0; l < p.length; l++){\n        p.eq(l).addClass([o.hoverClass,c.bcClass].join(' ')).filter('li:has(ul)').removeClass(o.pathClass);\n      }\n      sf.o[s] = sf.op = o;\n\n      $('li:has(ul)',this)[($.fn.hoverIntent && !o.disableHI) ? 'hoverIntent' : 'hover'](over,out).each(function() {\n        if (o.autoArrows) addArrow( $(this).children('a:first-child, span.nolink:first-child') );\n      })\n      .not('.'+c.bcClass)\n        .hideSuperfishUl();\n\n      var $a = $('a, span.nolink',this);\n      $a.each(function(i){\n        var $li = $a.eq(i).parents('li');\n        $a.eq(i).focus(function(){over.call($li);}).blur(function(){out.call($li);});\n      });\n      o.onInit.call(this);\n\n    }).each(function() {\n      var menuClasses = [c.menuClass],\n      addShadow = true;\n      if ($.browser !== undefined){\n        if ($.browser.msie && $.browser.version < 7){\n          addShadow = false;\n        }\n      }\n      if (sf.op.dropShadows && addShadow){\n        menuClasses.push(c.shadowClass);\n      }\n      $(this).addClass(menuClasses.join(' '));\n    });\n  };\n\n  var sf = $.fn.superfish;\n  sf.o = [];\n  sf.op = {};\n  sf.IE7fix = function(){\n    var o = sf.op;\n    if ($.browser !== undefined){\n      if ($.browser.msie && $.browser.version > 6 && o.dropShadows && o.animation.opacity != undefined) {\n        this.toggleClass(sf.c.shadowClass+'-off');\n      }\n    }\n  };\n  sf.c = {\n    bcClass: 'sf-breadcrumb',\n    menuClass: 'sf-js-enabled',\n    anchorClass: 'sf-with-ul',\n    arrowClass: o.$path : '';\n      o.retainPath = false;\n      var $ul = $(['li.',o.hoverClass].join(''),this).add(this).not(not).removeClass(o.hoverClass)\n          .children('ul').addClass('sf-hidden');\n .children('ul.sf-hidden').hide().removeClass('sf-hidden');\n      sf.IE7fix.call($ul);\n      o.onBeforeShow.call($ul);\n      $ul.animate(o.animation,o.speed,function(){ sf.IE7fix.call($ul);
